This paper deals with the robustness of machine learning classifiers, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. However, the focus on non-parametric methods and the use of nearest neighbors and kernel classifiers suggest that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of adversarial examples, which is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The mention of histograms and data distributions suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision) may also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the use of well-separated data and Adversarial Pruning suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) may be a relevant sub-category as well.
